    "summary": "High-performing leader with 20+ years of experience in the tech sector. Passionate about making society digitally more safe with cyber threat intelligence, innovation and creating a strategic impact.\n\nWith a Bachelor Business Sudies, Master  Organisational Sociology from Erasmus University and Master Cyber security from Leiden University I am able to combine business strategy, policy goals, cyber security external developments, overcoming various organisational impediments to fulfil customer requirements on cyber risk management.\n\nConsistently achieved stretch goals in multi stakeholder environment in different roles, such as co-founder of the Dutch National Detection Network and building long term collaborations with customers and partners. Ready and able to adjust to changing needs of the business, customers and our security professionals. \n\nSeasoned in briefing senior executives on business plans to increase value for our customers and impact on society. While also being successful in front of technical audience clarifying the strategic course in desired technical solutions and process.\n \nAble to lead a variety of teams and disciplines and comfortable to work both at the technical, tactical and strategic level, in the public and private sector. Expertise in leading and directly managing teams to drive a unified strategy, harmonius vision and solid execution.\n\nTop strengths include effective communication, strategic thinking, accountabity to deliver meaningful results and being a trusted advisor to senior executives and customers. Key technology focus includes areas such as cloud, end point, zero trust, threat actors, techniques and procedures, data science, and risk management.",
